    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4 text-slate-800">What is iTalki?</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">iTalki is the world's largest language tutoring marketplace. It connects learners with over 10,000 tutors from 100+ countries. iTalki offers two types of tutors:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-600 mb-4">
      <li><strong>Community tutors:</strong> Native speakers who teach casually. Prices start at $5/hour. No formal teaching qualifications required.</li>
      <li><strong>Professional tutors:</strong> Qualified teachers with formal training. Prices typically $15-$50/hour.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">iTalki is known for its flexibility. You book lessons directly with tutors, choose your own schedule, and can switch tutors easily.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4 text-slate-800">What is Preply?</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Preply is also a tutoring marketplace, but with a stronger focus on structured learning. It offers a built-in curriculum and trial lessons before committing to a tutor.</p>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Preply categorizes tutors into:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-600 mb-4">
      <li><strong>Community tutors:</strong> Similar to iTalki, native speakers teaching casually.</li>
      <li><strong>Certified tutors:</strong> Tutors with verified teaching certificates (TEFL, CELTA, etc.).</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Preply's trial lesson feature ($2-5 for 20 minutes) lets you test a tutor's teaching style before booking regular sessions.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4 text-slate-800">Pricing Comparison</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Both platforms have wide price ranges depending on tutor type and experience.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-3 text-slate-800">iTalki Pricing</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-600 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Community tutors:</strong> $5-$15/hour</li>
      <li><strong>Professional tutors:</strong> $15-$50/hour</li>
      <li><strong>Trial lessons:</strong> Free (community) or paid (professional)</li>
      <li><strong>Lesson packages:</strong> Buy 5+ lessons for 5-15% discount</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-3 text-slate-800">Preply Pricing</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-600 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Community tutors:</strong> $10-$25/hour</li>
      <li><strong>Certified tutors:</strong> $25-$80/hour</li>
      <li><strong>Trial lessons:</strong> ~$2-5 for 20 minutes</li>
      <li><strong>Lesson packages:</strong> Discounts for bulk purchases</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Winner:</strong> iTalki for budget learners. Community tutors start at $5/hour, compared to Preply's $10/hour minimum.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4 text-slate-800">Tutor Quality</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>iTalki:</strong> Quality varies significantly between community and professional tutors. Community tutors may have excellent English but limited teaching skills. Professional tutors have verified qualifications but cost more.</p>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Preply:</strong> Similar quality variance, but Preply's "Certified" filter makes it easier to find qualified teachers. The trial lesson system helps you verify quality before committing.</p>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed"><strong>Winner:</strong> Tie. Both platforms require careful tutor selection. Use reviews and trial lessons on either platform.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4 text-slate-800">Features Comparison</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>iTalki extras:</strong></p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-600 mb-4">
      <li>iTalki Notebook — built-in vocabulary builder</li>
      <li>Community conversations — free group speaking practice</li>
      <li>Instant tutoring — book lessons with available tutors immediately</li>
      <li>Flexible scheduling — tutors set their own availability</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Preply extras:</strong></p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-600 mb-6">
      <li>Learning path — structured curriculum for goal-oriented learners</li>
      <li>Trial lessons — test before you commit</li>
      <li>Progress tracking — monitor your improvement over time</li>
      <li>Corporate plans — team learning for businesses</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4 text-slate-800">User Experience</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>iTalki:</strong> Clean, functional interface. Filter tutors by price, rating, availability, and specialty. Video calls use integrated Zoom-style technology. The mobile apps work well for booking and rescheduling.</p>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed"><strong>Preply:</strong> Modern, polished interface. Better built-in learning materials. The "find your perfect tutor" quiz helps new users narrow down options. Slightly smoother user experience overall.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4 text-slate-800">iTalki Pros and Cons</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
      <div class="bg-emerald-900/30 border border-emerald-700 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-emerald-400 mb-4">Pros</h3>
