    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4 text-slate-800">Preply Pros and Cons</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
      <div class="bg-blue-900/30 border border-blue-700 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-blue-400 mb-4">Pros</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-neutral-300">
          <li>Trial lessons before committing</li>
          <li>Structured learning path</li>
          <li>Certified tutor filter</li>
          <li>Better user interface</li>
          <li>Progress tracking features</li>
          <li>Corporate team plans</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-red-900/30 border border-red-700 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-red-400 mb-4">Cons</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-neutral-300">
          <li>Higher minimum price ($10/hr)</li>
          <li>Less scheduling flexibility</li>
          <li>Smaller marketplace</li>
          <li>No free community option</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4 text-slate-800">Who Should Choose iTalki?</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-600 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Budget learners:</strong> Community tutors from $5/hour</li>
      <li><strong>Flexible schedules:</strong> Need evening or weekend lessons</li>
      <li><strong>Casual practice:</strong> Want conversation without strict curriculum</li>
      <li><strong>Instant lessons:</strong> Can't plan ahead, need on-demand availability</li>
      <li><strong>Variety seekers:</strong> Want to try many different tutors</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4 text-slate-800">Who Should Choose Preply?</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-600 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Goal-oriented learners:</strong> Want a structured path with progress tracking</li>
      <li><strong>Careful choosers:</strong> Prefer to test tutors via trial lessons first</li>
      <li><strong>Quality-first learners:</strong> Willing to pay more for certified teachers</li>
      <li><strong>Corporate users:</strong> Need team learning plans for employees</li>
      <li><strong>Beginners:</strong> Want guidance on which tutor level to start with</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4 text-slate-800">Final Verdict</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>iTalki wins for:</strong> Budget learners, flexible scheduling, and casual conversation practice. The $5/hour starting price makes quality tutoring accessible to everyone.</p>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Preply wins for:</strong> Structured learners who want curriculum guidance, trial lessons, and certified teacher verification.</p>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8 leading-relaxed">Both platforms are legitimate and have helped millions of learners improve their English. The "right" choice depends on your budget, learning style, and goals. If you're unsure, start with iTalki's free community tutors to get comfortable with online lessons, then upgrade to professional tutors when you're ready.</p>

